<document id="31175859"><sentence text="Experience with therapeutic drug monitoring of three antifungal agents using an LC-MS/MS method in routine clinical practice." /><sentence text="Therapeutic drug monitoring (TDM) of voriconazole, itraconazole, and posaconazole is a useful tool for treatment of fungal infections"><entity charOffset="37-49" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="51-63" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e1" text="itraconazole" /><entity charOffset="69-81" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e2" text="posaconazole" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s2.e2" /></sentence><sentence text=" We validated a simple and reliable LC-MS/MS method using simple protein precipitation for simultaneous determination of voriconazole, itraconazole, and posaconazole"><entity charOffset="121-133" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="135-147" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e1" text="itraconazole" /><entity charOffset="153-165" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e2" text="posaconazole" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s3.e2" /></sentence><sentence text=" The linearity, accuracy, precision, carryover, and matrix effects were validated" /><sentence text=" Total sample preparation time was &lt;30 min per batch, and analytical run time was 3" /><sentence text="8 min per sample" /><sentence text=" We also presented clinical experience of TDM at 1183 serum concentrations over one year using this validated assay method" /><sentence text=" About 77%, 85%, and 96% of measured voriconazole, itraconazole, and posaconazole concentrations were within the therapeutic range, respectively"><entity charOffset="37-49" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="51-63" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e1" text="itraconazole" /><entity charOffset="69-81" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e2" text="posaconazole" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s8.e2" /></sentence><sentence text=" The number of respective measurements per patient was 1-63, 1-8, and 1-4 for voriconazole, itraconazole, and posaconazole"><entity charOffset="78-90" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="92-104" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e1" text="itraconazole" /><entity charOffset="110-122" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e2" text="posaconazole" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s9.e2" /></sentence><sentence text=" All three antifungal agents showed large intra-individual variability (2 to 181% CV) and drug-drug interaction with proton pump inhibitors or rifampin"><entity charOffset="143-151" id="DDI-PubMed.31175859.s10.e0" text="rifampin" /></sentence><sentence text=" In conclusion, we developed and validated a simple and fast method that was successfully applied in a routine clinical setting" /><sentence text="" /></document>